<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="70" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[111,750,715,1315]" pageId="13" pageNumber="70">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[111,235,715,739]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="70">Remarks. –</emphasis>
This species was first assigned to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1871" box="[607,750,716,739]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pseudorhombilidae" genus="Micropanope" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[607,750,716,739]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="70">Micropanope</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Sakai (1965), but was later transferred to a new genus, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guinot" authorityYear="1967" box="[111,272,780,803]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Paraxanthodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[111,272,780,803]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="70">Paraxanthodes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by 
<bibRefCitation author="Guinot, D" box="[320,488,780,803]" pageId="13" pageNumber="70" pagination="149 - 166" refId="ref16270" refString="Guinot, D., 1967 b. Recherches preliminaires sur les groupements naturels chez les Crustaces Decapodes Brachyoures. IV. Observations sur quelques genres de Xanthidae. Bulletin du Museum national d'Histoire naurelle, 2 e serie, 39 (4): 149 - 166." type="journal article" year="1967">Guinot (1967b)</bibRefCitation>
, wherein she designated it as the 
<typeStatus box="[209,255,812,835]" pageId="13" pageNumber="70">type</typeStatus>
species. The Philippine material agrees well with the illustrations provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai, T" box="[483,683,844,867]" pageId="13" pageNumber="70" pagination="97 - 106" refId="ref19013" refString="Sakai, T., 1965 a. On two new genera and five new species of xanthoid crabs from the collection of His Majesty the Emperor of Japan made in Sagami Bay. Crustaceana, 8 (1): 97 - 106." type="journal article" year="1965">Sakai (1965a: 103</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[112,147,1945,1966]" captionTargetBox="[111,1449,603,1928]" captionTargetId="figure-19@7.[111,1449,603,1928]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 2. Live colouration of euxanthine crabs from the Philippines: A, Hypocolpus haanii Rathbun, 1909, male juv., (11.5 × 8.0 mm) (B11, Pamilacan Is., ZRC 2008.1383); B, Ladomedaeus fungillus Manuel-Santos &amp; Ng, 2007, male juv. (9.7 × 7.0 mm) (CP2708, ZRC 2008.1389); C, Miersiella cavifrons Takeda, 1989, male (9.8 × 6.6 mm) (L36, Panglao Is., ZRC 2008.1391); D, Paramedaeus globosus Serène &amp; Vadon, 1981, male (6.0 × 4.6 mm) (T36, Cervera Shoal, MNHN-B31891); E, Paramedaeus simplex (A. Milne-Edwards, 1873), female (9.7 × 6.8 mm) (S7, Panglao Is., NMCR-27356); F, Paraxanthodes obtusidens (Sakai, 1965), male (18.6 × 13.0 mm) (CP2747, ZRC 2008.1410)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5342425" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5342425/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="70">Figs. 2c</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[148,195,876,899]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[111,146,2004,2025]" captionTargetBox="[111,1448,650,1972]" captionTargetId="figure-85@9.[111,1448,650,1974]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 3. Hypocolpus abbotti (Rathbun, 1894), male, (41.6 by 28.7 mm) (Balicasag Is., MNHN-B31888): A, dorsal view; B, fronto-lateral view of subhepatic cavity; Hypocolpus haanii Rathbun, 1909, male (49.5 × 34.5 mm) (Balicasag Is., NMCR-27339); C, dorsal view; D, fronto-lateral view of subhepatic cavity; Hypocolpus kurodai Takeda, 1980, male (21.0 × 13.5 mm) (Marinduque, NMCR-6609); E, dorsal view; F, fronto-lateral view of subhepatic cavity." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5342427" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5342427/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="70">3e, f</figureCitation>
) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Guinot, D" box="[253,516,876,899]" pageId="13" pageNumber="70" pagination="149 - 166" refId="ref16270" refString="Guinot, D., 1967 b. Recherches preliminaires sur les groupements naturels chez les Crustaces Decapodes Brachyoures. IV. Observations sur quelques genres de Xanthidae. Bulletin du Museum national d'Histoire naurelle, 2 e serie, 39 (4): 149 - 166." type="journal article" year="1967">Guinot (1967b: 723–726</bibRefCitation>
, Figs. 51a, b, 59). The live colouration is as follows; the carapace and chelipeds and ambulatory legs are deep reddish-orange, with lighter areas of yellowish-white immediately surrounding the third and fourth anterolateral teeth. There are small patches of white particularly in the cardiac region and in the grooves between the bases of 2M and 
<specimenCount box="[341,385,1068,1091]" pageId="13" pageNumber="70" type="generic">3M.</specimenCount>
The fingers of the chela are dark brown all throughout their length, but not extending to the palm. Other than the 
<typeStatus box="[347,393,1132,1155]" pageId="13" pageNumber="70">type</typeStatus>
locality (Sagami Bay, 
<collectingCountry box="[649,714,1132,1155]" name="Japan" pageId="13" pageNumber="70">Japan</collectingCountry>
), it has also been recorded from Muroto-zaki, Kii Nagashima, Kii Minabe, and Tosa Bay, all in 
<collectingCountry box="[501,563,1196,1219]" name="Japan" pageId="13" pageNumber="70">Japan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Yokoya, Y" box="[582,744,1196,1219]" pageId="13" pageNumber="70" pagination="1 - 226" refId="ref20012" refString="Yokoya, Y., 1933. On the distribution of decapod crustaceans inhabiting the continental shelf around Japan, chiefly based upon the materials collected by S. S. Soyo-Maru, during the years 1923 - 1930. Journal of the College of Agriculture, Tokyo Imperial University, 12 (1): 1 - 226." type="journal article" year="1933">Yokoya, 1933</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai, T" box="[111,258,1228,1251]" pageId="13" pageNumber="70" pagination="1 - 92" refId="ref19058" refString="Sakai, T., 1965 b. The Crabs of Sagami Bay, collected by His Majesty the Emperor of Japan. Maruzen Co., Tokyo. i - xvi, 1 - 206, (English text), Figs. 1 - 27, Pls. 1 - 100: 1 - 92 [Japanese text]: 1 - 26 [references and index in English]: 27 - 32 [index in Japanese], 1 map." type="book chapter" year="1965">Sakai, 1965b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sakai, T" box="[273,331,1228,1251]" pageId="13" pageNumber="70" refId="ref19143" refString="Sakai, T., 1976 a. Crabs of Japan and the Adjacent Seas. Kodansha Ltd, Tokyo. [In 3 volumes]: (1) English text: i - xxix, 1 - 773, Figs 1 - 379, (2) Plates volume: 1 - 16, Pls 1 - 251, (3) Japanese text: 1 - 461, Figs 1 - 2, 3 maps.)" type="book" year="1976">1976</bibRefCitation>
), and also from the South 
<collectingCountry box="[636,700,1228,1251]" name="China" pageId="13" pageNumber="70">China</collectingCountry>
Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Guinot, D" box="[118,281,1260,1283]" pageId="13" pageNumber="70" pagination="149 - 166" refId="ref16270" refString="Guinot, D., 1967 b. Recherches preliminaires sur les groupements naturels chez les Crustaces Decapodes Brachyoures. IV. Observations sur quelques genres de Xanthidae. Bulletin du Museum national d'Histoire naurelle, 2 e serie, 39 (4): 149 - 166." type="journal article" year="1967">Guinot, 1967b</bibRefCitation>
). This is the first record of this species in the 
<collectingCountry box="[151,275,1292,1315]" name="Philippines" pageId="13" pageNumber="70">Philippines</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
